<note xml:id="ch26n67"><p id="ch26n67pa1">The passage of the Danube is exposed by Ammianus (xxxi. 3, 4), Zosimus (l. iv. p. 223, 224), Eunapius (in Excerpt. Legat. p. 19, 20), and Jornandes (c. 25, 26). Ammianus declares (c. 5) that he means only ipsas rerum digerere <hi rend="italic">summitates.</hi> But he often takes a false measure of their importance; and his superfluous prolixity is disagreeably balanced by his unseasonable brevity.</p></note>

